CatDescriptText: Mrs. Margo Riley, 2538 Fifth Avenue, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 16, 1958, pg. 3 with question: "Do you think that Negroes are giving sufficient financial help to the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People?" answer reads: "No, I think that we are giving quite enough. We are giving what we can but that is not enough."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of  Margo Riley in floral dress, with handbag over left arm, standing in front of store window with mannequins, dresses, and several women window shopping in background
